The paper proposes a novel approach for approximating the partition function of graphical models (GMs) using spectral methods. This involves utilizing the global spectral feature of GMs and designing a spectral mean-field scheme. These techniques are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves computational complexity and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
